b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48468.htm)  [Next](sbe48470.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n22\\. And on account of the words denoting becoming.\n\nThat the texts under discussion have an injunctive purport also follows from\nthe fact that they contain verbal forms denoting becoming or origination--'he\nis to meditate' and the like; for all such forms have injunctive force. All\nthese texts therefore are meant to enjoin special forms of meditation.--Here\nterminates the adhikara _n_ a of mere glorification.'\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 23. .. the stories told in the Upanishads ...](sbe48470.htm)\n\n"